{"name": "salinic", "metadata": {"name": "salinic", "version": "0.6.1", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pydantic", "requests", "glom"], "summary": "Search abstraction layer", "upload_time": 1733864000}, "documentation": ["[![Tests](https://github.com/papermerge/salinic/actions/workflows/tests.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/papermerge/salinic/actions/workflows/tests.yml)\n\n# Salinic\n\nSalinic - provides modular search. It features a unified API that\nallows you to plug in different search backends.\nCurrently, it supports Xapian and Solr backends.\n\n\n## Usage\n\nDeclare your search schema:\n\n    from typing import Optional\n    from typing_extensions import Annotated\n\n    from salinic.field import IdField, KeywordField, TextField\n    from salinic.schema import Schema\n\n\n    class MyModel(Schema):\n        \"\"\"Index schema\"\"\"\n        id: Annotated[str, IdField(primary_key=True)]\n        user_id: str\n        parent_id: str\n        title: Annotated[str, TextField()]\n        text: Annotated[Optional[str], TextField()] = None\n        tags: Annotated[Optional[list[str]], KeywordField()] = []\n\n\nIndex your documents:\n\n        from salinic import IndexRW, create_engine\n\n        engine = create_engine(\"xapian:////search_index\")\n        index = IndexRW(engine, schema=MyModel)\n\n        for document in all_your_documents():\n            model = MyModel(\n                id=str(document.id),\n                user_id=str(document.user_id),\n                parent_id=document.parent_id,\n                title=document.title,\n                text=document.text,\n                tags=document.tags\n            )\n            index.add(model)\n\n\nSearch your documents:\n\n        from salinic import IndexRO, create_engine\n\n        engine = create_engine(\"xapian:////search_index\")\n        index = IndexRO(engine, schema=MyModel)\n\n        sq = Search(MyModel).query(\" your query string \")\n\n        for found in index.search(sq):\n            print(found)  # found is instance of MyModel\n\n\nThe only modification of your for changing to different search\nengine backend, is the first argument of the `create_engine` method e.g. from\n\"xapian:////search_index\" to \"solr://localhost:8983/my-index-name\".\n"], "modules": [{"name": "salinic.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "salinic.utils.get_db_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dsn", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "salinic.utils.first", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "iterable", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "condition", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns first item in the iterable matching condition\n\nIf there is no condition provided just return first item.\nIf there is no matching item or iterable is empty - just return None"]}, {"name": "salinic.utils.trim_suffixes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "some_dict", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "salinic.utils.filter_keys", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "some_dict", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "keys_to_filter", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "salinic.url", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "salinic.url.make_url", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "name_or_url", "type": {"name": "str | URL", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "URL", "xref": {"fqname": "salinic.url.URL", "project": null}, "params": null}, "docu